    <h1>North Sikkim Itinerary - 4 Days, 3 Nights</h1>







    <h2>Day 1: Arrival in Gangtok</h2>



    <p>Upon arrival in Gangtok, check-in at your hotel and take some time to rest. In the afternoon, visit the following attractions:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>MG Marg</strong> - Explore the bustling shopping street of Gangtok.</li>



      <li><strong>Enchey Monastery</strong> - Visit the peaceful monastery and enjoy the views.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Return to your hotel for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







    <h2>Day 2: Gangtok to Lachen</h2>



    <p>After breakfast, check-out from the hotel and proceed to Lachen. On the way, visit:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>Tashi Viewpoint</strong> - Enjoy panoramic views of the Kanchenjunga range.</li>



      <li><strong>Seven Sisters Waterfall</strong> - A beautiful waterfall surrounded by lush greenery.</li>



      <li><strong>Naga Waterfall</strong> - Another scenic waterfall en route to Lachen.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Upon arrival in Lachen, check-in at your hotel for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







    <h2>Day 3: Lachen to Lachung via Gurudongmar Lake, and Kala Pathhar</h2>



    <p>Early morning, drive to Gurudongmar Lake, one of the highest lakes in the world. Then visit the famous Kala Pathhar, from where the Everest Base Camp can be viewed. After spending some time, return to Lachen for lunch. Post lunch, proceed to Lachung. Upon arrival, check-in at your hotel for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







    <h2>Day 4: Lachung to Yumthang Valley, and Zero Point and Return to Gangtok</h2>



    <p>After breakfast, visit Yumthang Valley, also known as the Valley of Flowers. Also visit snow-capped Zero Point, beyond which there are no civilian roads. On the way back, visit:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>Hot Springs</strong> - Take a dip in the natural hot springs known for their medicinal properties.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Return to Lachung for lunch and then proceed to Gangtok for your onward journey in the evening.</p>







